Project Overview:
A fully offline, desktop-based password manager built in Java, using SQLite as our local database via JDBC. All data remains on the user's device at all times — no network connectivity required.

Proposed Feature Set:
• Front-end GUI (Java Swing or JavaFX) — Login screen, vault dashboard, add/edit entry forms
• Back-end encryption engine — AES-256-GCM for authenticated encryption of stored passwords
• PBKDF2 with a high iteration count and random salt for master password key derivation
• Post-quantum considerations — AES-256 is already considered quantum-resistant under NIST guidance (Grover's algorithm reduces it to ~128-bit security, which remains safe). We plan to document this and explore CRYSTALS-Kyber (NIST FIPS 203) for the key encapsulation layer, time permitting
• Password Generator using Java's SecureRandom
• Session auto-lock and clipboard auto-clear for runtime security
• Database: SQLite (local .db file). No passwords or master key material are ever written to disk in plaintext.

